<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-07-10"><hi rend="italic">July 10, 1897</hi></date>.
                                (Received Aug. 16.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2774.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose a copy of a
                            dispatch which was sent by me to the Tsung-li Yamên the 10th instant, on
                            the subject of the prevention of antiforeign riots.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Denby.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>